wikipedia_page.main: James Phillip Austin (December 8, 1879 – March 6, 1965) was a Welsh-American professional baseball player and coach. He played in Major League Baseball as a third baseman for the New York Highlanders and St. Louis Browns from 1909 through 1923, 1925 through 1926, and 1929. He also managed the Browns in 1913, 1918, and 1923.
